@Node Usage "Boards.library: Usage"

@{U}  USAGE  @{UU}

There are two seperate scripts and a datafile. The datafile,
STOCKLIST.RXDATA, simply contains a list of the EPIC stock code and the
Name of the stock (which must be identical to the stock as used in
AmiBrokerRexx) seperated by a few spaces and with a return between each
entry. The scripts expect to find this file in the path
RExxscripts:Stocklist.rxdata. If you wish to store the list somewhere else,
you should either add an Assign or alter the scripts.

The GETQUOTE Script causes IBrowse to read the data file and search the
Electronic Share Information site for a listing on that stock. This is then
saved as an HTML file to RAM. Unfortunately, due to limitations in
IBrowse's ARexx interface, you will have to manually press return for each
save requester that appears.

The MAKEDATA Script reads in the HTML files and converts them into an
AMiBroker ASCII data file. This script strips out all the information in
the HTML file. As I'm not in charge of the way ESI construct their web
pages, it may be necessary to alter this in the future. I will be posting
updates when necessary to deal with this problem.

There are two scripts instead of one because it is more forgiving. The
MAKEDATA script takes only a few seconds to run, but downloading the HTML
can take minutes. As the data file would be incomplete (and return an
error) if all the files were not present, it's best to run this script
after you are sure all the HTML has been downloaded. Of course, I could
cunningly make the script more complicated to check for this, but I can't
be bothered at the moment...




NOTE: The date given to the stock data is taken from the Amiga's system
clock. Make sure your clock is set to the right date!




@EndNode
@Node Requirements "Requirements"

@{U}  REQUIRED  @{UU}

 To make use of these scripts they way they were intended you will need:


@{B}IBrowse@{UB} - The script could be adapted for other ARexx capable
browsers.
@{B}AmiBroker@{UB} - available from Aminet. You will need to register if
you want to save your data too...
@{B}ARexx@{UB} - rather obviously.

You will also need to register on the esi site (www.esi.co.uk), but even
the free membership will give you access to the stock data.










@EndNode
